
    THABO MOKGATLE, secretary of Royal Bafokeng’s Lekgotla la Kgosing, has raised the lid on fraud and corruption allegations that have dogged financially-troubled Premier Soccer League (PSL) side, Platinum Stars.Mokgatle, in his personal capacity, has opened a case of fraud, corrupt activities, money laundering, illicit dealings and racketeering, against five senior employees of the club, who are known to SunSport.The case was opened at Phokeng Police Station, in Rustenburg, North West, on Wednesday. And because of its seriousness, it was referred to the Commercial Crimes Unit, where investigations are currently underway.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvvCv4CidLXW7hsh4SF5j33HDE8Z_Y1UOcdeoJCUr5PEFgfhETTTaYX7_QTSUW7GTIy8TL0lrkoQh82W8V34C9XW9C2HzDtLORhl0WTJpp2K8xFcmaZ7A55km9ndmkjU3-Q1R44W2hOYPueCpQy1TFvip6XgDTMQRKtwpTnj5P6SFXilZwoNCvson5lsiMvUFOVGml_Hu_LMHuHWHfVHi_XBzGNIqc5P9K0FNsMZYREi8JeypyZfrnMgownoE2Ev-QPhhHyNN2mSX5xCzrZ\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzCzHZegUPIzKEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
